30/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Costas Karamanlis, leader of the main opposition party New Democracy (ND), presented on Monday (29 September) his party's programme to reform the state sector and local government. 
He said the programme would be based on transparency and would aim to eliminate corruption and bureaucracy. 
Karamanlis also reiterated ND's readiness to launch new social policies and a new local administration model if it wins the spring parliamentary elections. 
(ANA, MPA - 29/09/03)
